title: Grateful Dead Live at St. Paul Civic Center on 1982-08-06
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Minglewood Blues-> Candyman, Little Red Rooster, Bird Song, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, It's All Over Now, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication-> Might As Well

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Johnny B. Goode, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: excellent Matrix nice Bird Song, Tennessee, Scarlet/Fire.

An A level matrix As far as the job done by Hunter. It's sounds lovely.

The set list is frankly a bit iffy for me- but Bird Song and the first half of set 2 (esp. S/F) are very good.

Fun Can someone post a aud of the Kiel show after the starlight. Must be a copy of 2 or 3 out there somewhere. 
 This show here is one that kind of fly's under the radar only because this tour had so many hot shows. I think people tend to over look this show. Iowa gets a lot of attention. But this St Paul show was a blast great set list great sound.. My very 1st time catching entire tour and would love a aud copy of the kiel just to complete the collection

First Tape This was one of the first soundboard tapes I ever had.  A TDK SA90, and although it has had several rudimentary surgeries with scotch tape splicing it still plays!

I've always wondered who Scott Anthony Williams was and what the hell was going on that caused Bob to announce the emergency message for him.  Ooooooh.  Sounds like the fodder for a bad trip!

"Wait, did Bob just say my name…."

Best of the best Great show lovingly remastered by Hunter Seamons.

Right here for you to enjoy.
